## 📌 Program 1: Print "Hello, World!"

### 💻 Code

```c id="k2m8xp"
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!");
    return 0;
}
```

### 📖 Explanation

* `#include <stdio.h>` → Used for input/output functions
* `int main()` → Entry point of the program
* `printf("Hello, World!");` → Prints the message
* `return 0;` → Ends the program successfully

### ✅ Output

```id="n7q4vs"
Hello, World!
```

